#step 1 Install and create postgre DB
    sudo apt install postgresql 
    #switch to postgres User and launch postgre
       $ sudo -i -u postgres
       $ psql
    #change password since the postregres password is your super user one
        ALTER USER postgres WITH PASSWORD 'myNewSecurePassword';
    #create a Db
        CREATE DATABASE mydb;
#step 2 download and install CLI prisma
     $ npm install prisma --save-dev
     if there is no prisma folder create one with the command and you will find inside prisma.schema file where you can set the name of the db and the several table. 
      $ npx prisma init
you will also find a .env file where lives the URL of the DB which link the DB to prisma 
    DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:PORT/DATABASENAME?schema=public"
    with the information above :
    DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:myNewSecurePassword@localhost:5432/mydb?schema=public"

Finally to apply the schema modification to the db run this command
    $ npx prisma migrate dev
You can also inject SQL command in migration file